verbose_text: Robo1 is a transmembrane receptor with a key role in determining whether an mAL neuron develops the ILN or not; Robo1 inhibits formation of the ILN in females, whereas robo1 is transcriptionally repressed by FruBM in males so that the ILN forms in some mAL neurons.
evidence: Robo1 inhibits formation of the ILN
